==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Treadle
<hw>Trea"dle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>tredyl</ets> a step, AS. <ets>tredel</ets>. See
<er>Tread</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The part of a foot lathe, or
other machine, which is pressed or moved by the foot.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>The chalaza of a bird's egg; the
tread.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Treadmill</ent>⟦br⟧
